They celebrated their 18th we'd
ding anniversary recently.


Mrs. Bobbie Ross spent the
weekend with her brother,
Tommie Dilworth.


Mrs. Betty Powers, of Denver
is a winter visitor here.


Plan to come to the afternoon
Of singing Sum-, Dec. 10, 3 pm.
at Shiloh Baptist Church, 9l7
w. Buckeye.


Rev. S. T. Miller welcomes
everyone. Mrs. Thelma Whitfield
is the program chairman.


Some of the guests soloists in
clude Mrs. Mary Bradford and
Clarence Davis.


Peeping into 1865 = The Debon-
airs are making big plans for
their annual Thank You Dance.
1t will be a formal (strictly)
scheduled late in January.
Everything will be free for the
friends who have supported our
programs.


Willing Workers Unionzwill
hold two nights of song every
second and third Saturdays. 1t
will be citywide. Chairmen are
Miss Joyce Singleton and me.

that toothache Big Daddy of KCAC

haps hinder folks from lying.

After 20 years of mar.
riage, a Bodmersham, Eng
land, retired soldier left his
wife and four children and
moved into a cave. He has
rugged his cave with Wall-to.
wall carpeting, pictures of
his family, a table and a bed.
